            AppRoutes = """["/reports"]""",
            Tags = """["reports","reference","advanced"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Report Cheat Sheet\n\nA quick guide to the 28 ready-made reports — what each one answers and whether it needs a date range. Reports marked **(date range)** show From and To pickers at the top.\n\n- **Jobs by Stage** — how many jobs are in each stage (bar).\n- **Overdue Jobs** — jobs past their due date (table).\n- **Job Completion Trend** — finishes over time (line, date range).\n- **On-Time Delivery** — share delivered on or before the due date (date range).\n- **Average Lead Time** — average days from start to finish, by job type.\n- **Time in Stage** — how long jobs sit in each stage.\n- **Job Margin** — revenue against cost, per job.\n- **Cycle Review** / **My Cycle Summary** — planning-cycle results (whole shop / just you).\n- **R&D Report** — activity on research and tooling work.\n- **Time by User** / **My Time Log** — hours logged (date range; personal version).\n- **Team Workload** — who's assigned what right now.\n- **Employee Productivity** — output per person.\n- **My Work History** — your own finished work.\n- **Expense Summary** / **My Expense History** — spending by category (date range; personal version).\n- **Lead Pipeline** — leads counted by status.\n- **Customer Activity** — how engaged each customer is.\n- **AR Aging** — money owed to you, grouped by how overdue it is.\n- **Revenue** / **Profit & Loss** — income over time / income against expenses (date range).\n- **Quote-to-Close** — how often and how fast quotes turn into orders.\n- **Lead-to-Sales** — how leads move toward a sale.\n- **Shipping Summary** — shipment volume and which carriers you use.\n- **Inventory Levels** — how much stock you have on hand.\n- **Maintenance** — equipment upkeep activity and cost.\n- **Quality/Scrap** — scrap rates and inspection results.\n\nThe personal reports (My Work History, My Time Log, My Expense History, My Cycle Summary) are the only reports Engineers and Production Workers can see, and they reach them from their own pages rather than the Reports page.\n\n## Sharing a Saved Report\n\nEach saved report belongs to the person who made it and has a switch for whether others can see it.\n\n- **What's in the saved list.** Your saved-report menu shows both your own reports and any report someone else has shared, newest changes first. A report shared by a coworker still appears for you, marked with their name.\n- **The share switch.** On means everyone who can see reports (Admins, Managers, Office Managers, PMs) can find it. Off means only you can. You set the switch when you save, and you can change it later.\n- **Changing or deleting.** Open a shared report, change it, and click Save — it updates the same report. The red trash icon deletes it. There's no separate \"save a copy\"; saving overwrites the report you opened.\n- **Sharing is all-or-nothing.** A report is either just yours or open to everyone who can see reports. There's no way to share with only one team or role.\n\n## Three Filters Worth Knowing\n\nThree filters work a little differently from a plain match:\n\n- **Between** — a range on numbers and dates, including both ends. You enter a low and a high value; leaving one out won't work. Handy for a date window or a price range.\n- **Is one of** — for choice fields like status. Type a list separated by commas (like Open, In Progress, On Hold), and a row matches if it equals any of them. Cleaner than stacking several 'Is' filters.\n- **Is empty** / **Is filled in** — check whether a field has a value at all. You don't type anything for these. 'Is empty' finds records that were never filled in, such as jobs with no due date — which is different from matching a blank space.\n\nNot every filter fits every field. 'Contains' and 'Starts with' are for text; the more/less and Between filters are for numbers and dates; 'Is one of' is for choice fields; and 'Is', 'Is not', 'Is empty', and 'Is filled in' work on anything.\n\n## What the Results Table Can Do\n\nThe table under a report works like tables elsewhere in the app, so its handy features apply here too:\n\n- **Sort** — click a heading to sort; click again to reverse.\n- **Filter a column** — type in the column's filter box to narrow what you see.\n- **Show or hide columns** — pick which columns appear from the column menu; the report keeps your choice so it looks the same each time you open it.\n- **Paging** — long lists split into pages, 25 per page by default.\n- These features tidy the results already on screen. A CSV download always includes your chosen columns and every row, not just the page you're looking at.\n\n## Downloading a Saved Report\n\nBesides the CSV button while you're building, you can download a saved report straight from its menu. Choose the format you want — a spreadsheet file (CSV or Excel) or a PDF. Each download pulls the latest data, so a report you saved last month still shows this month's numbers. The same sharing rules apply: you can download your own reports and any that have been shared with you.\n\n## Emailing a Report on a Schedule\n\nInstead of opening a report to check it, you can have it emailed to you — and to anyone else — on a regular basis, so the numbers land in your inbox without you lifting a finger.\n\n- **Start from a saved report.** Scheduling works on a report you've already saved, so save (and maybe share) the report first.\n- **Choose who gets it.** Add the email addresses that should receive it — yourself, a coworker, your boss, a customer.\n- **Choose how often.** Set the cadence, such as every morning, every Monday, or the first of the month.\n- **Choose the format.** The report arrives as a spreadsheet (CSV or Excel) or a PDF, whichever you pick.\n- **Give it a subject line.** Optionally set the email's subject so recipients know at a glance what's inside.\n\nA scheduled report is a good fit for numbers someone needs on a rhythm — a weekly on-time-delivery summary to the plant manager, or a month-end expense report to the office manager.","sections":[]}"""
        });

        Log.Information("Seeded Reports training modules");
    }
}
